{"title_page": "1882 Men's Tennis tour", "text_new": "{{ Infobox tennis circuit season\n<!-- Details -->\n| name          = 1882 Men's tennis tour\n| image         = Richard sears.JPG\n| image_caption = Richard Sears pictured here won his 2nd consecutive U.S. National Championships this year\n| image_alt     = \n| image_size    = 200px\n| duration      = 24 April \u2013 12 November\n| edition       = 6th\n| tournaments   = 43 (Amateur)\n| categories    = Important (5) <br/> National (3) <br/> Regional/State (7) <br/> County (8)  <br/> Local (20)\n<!-- Achievements -->\n| most_tournament_titles       = {{flagicon|GBR}} [[Thomas Braddell#Robert Wallace Braddell|Robert W. Braddell]] (4)\n| most_tournament_finals       = {{flagicon|GBR}} [[Thomas Braddell#Robert Wallace Braddell|Robert W. Braddell]] (6)\n| prize_money_leader           = \n| points_leader                = \n<!-- Awards -->\n| player_of_the_year            = \n| most_improved_player_of_the_year = \n| newcomer_of_the_year             = \n| comeback_player_of_the_year      = \n| previous = [[1881 Men's Tennis tour|1881]]\n| next     = [[1883 Men's Tennis tour|1883]]\n}}\nThe '''1882 Men's tennis tour''' <ref>{{cite web|title=Tennis season 1882|url=https://app.thetennisbase.com/?enlace=season&anno=1882&tipoMainTorneos=main&surface=&tipo_de_torneo=|website=thetennisbase.com|publisher=The Tennis Base, 2016|accessdate=9 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Archives|first1=Tennis|title=Tournaments 1882|url=http://www.tennisarchives.com/jaarwedstrijdenfiche.php|website=www.tennisarchives.com|publisher=Tennis Archives, 2016|accessdate=9 December 2016}}</ref> was composed of the sixth annual pre-open era tour and now incorporated 43 events. The [[1882 Wimbledon Championships|Wimbledon Championships]] and [[Irish Open (tennis)|Irish Championships]] was won by [[William Renshaw]], the [[1882 U.S. National Championships (tennis)|U.S. National Championships]] was won by [[Richard Sears (tennis)|Richard Sears]] collecting his second title other big winners were Richard Taswell Richardson picking up the [[Manchester Open|Northern Lawn Tennis Championships]] and [[Ernest Renshaw]] winning the [[Princes Club Championships]], The title leader this season was [[Thomas Braddell#Robert Wallace Braddell|Robert W. Braddell]] winning 4 tournaments from 6 finals.\n\n==Calendar==\n'''Notes 1:''' Challenge Round: the final round of a tournament, in which the winner of a single-elimination phase faces the previous year's champion, who plays only that one match. The challenge round was used in the early history of tennis (from 1877 through 1921),<ref>{{cite web|title=Abolition of Challenge Rounds|url=https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/EP19220320.2.111.2?query=Paris%20International%20Championships|website=paperspast.natlib.govt.nz|publisher=EVENING POST, VOLUME CIII, ISSUE 65, 20 MARCH 1922|accessdate=6 October 2016}}</ref> in some tournaments not all.<center>* Indicates challenger</center>\n'''Notes 2''':''Tournaments in italics were events that were staged only once that season''\n\n===Key===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ffc;\"\n| '''Important tournaments''' <ref>{{cite book|last1=Mazak|first1=Karoly|title=The Concise History of Tennis, The complete tennis history from 1877|date=2016|publisher=Karoly  Mazak|pages=5\u201311|edition=6th|url=http://www.theconcisehistoryoftennis.com/|accessdate=9 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Nauright|first1=John|last2=Parrish|first2=Charles|title=Sports Around the World: History, Culture, and Practice|date=2012|publisher=ABC-CLIO|location=Santa Barbara, Calif.|isbn=9781598843002|page=198|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IkLYDgTnMxEC&pg=RA1-PA198&lpg=RA1-PA198&dq=notable+19th+century+tennis+tournaments&source=bl&ots=6SE1ULypjh&sig=JC623Xs4UpGTCsaRpaT--i6IJNY&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwitjanr3ffPAhXDMY8KHT6yALsQ6AEIUzAJ#v=onepage&q=notable%2019th%20century%20tennis%20tournaments&f=false|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite 