te web|last1=Archives|first1=Tennis|title=Tournaments 1882|url=http://www.tennisarchives.com/jaarwedstrijdenfiche.php|website=www.tennisarchives.com|publisher=Tennis Archives, 2016|accessdate=9 December 2016}}</ref> was composed of the sixth annual pre-open era tour and now incorporated 43 events. The [[1882 Wimbledon Championships|Wimbledon Championships]] and [[Irish Open (tennis)|Irish Championships]] was won by [[William Renshaw]], the [[1882 U.S. National Championships (tennis)|U.S. National Championships]] was won by [[Richard Sears (tennis)|Richard Sears]] collecting his second title other big winners were Richard Taswell Richardson picking up the [[Manchester Open|Northern Lawn Tennis Championships]] and [[Ernest Renshaw]] winning the [[Princes Club Championships]], The title leader this season was [[Thomas Braddell#Robert Wallace Braddell|Robert W. Braddell]] winning 4 tournaments from 6 finals.\n\n==Calendar==\n'''Notes 1:''' Challenge Round: the final round of a tournament, in which the winner of a single-elimination phase faces the previous year's champion, who plays only that one match. The challenge round was used in the early history of tennis (from 1877 through 1921),<ref>{{cite web|title=Abolition of Challenge Rounds|url=https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/EP19220320.2.111.2?query=Paris%20International%20Championships|website=paperspast.natlib.govt.nz|publisher=EVENING POST, VOLUME CIII, ISSUE 65, 20 MARCH 1922|accessdate=6 October 2016}}</ref> in some tournaments not all.<center>* Indicates challenger</center>\n'''Notes 2''':''Tournaments in italics were events that were staged only once that season''\n\n===Key===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ffc;\"\n| '''Important tournaments''' <ref>{{cite book|last1=Mazak|first1=Karoly|title=The Concise History of Tennis, The complete tennis history from 1877|date=2016|publisher=Karoly  Mazak|pages=5\u201311|edition=6th|url=http://www.theconcisehistoryoftennis.com/|accessdate=9 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Nauright|first1=John|last2=Parrish|first2=Charles|title=Sports Around the World: History, Culture, and Practice|date=2012|publisher=ABC-CLIO|location=Santa Barbara, Calif.|isbn=9781598843002|page=198|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IkLYDgTnMxEC&pg=RA1-PA198&lpg=RA1-PA198&dq=notable+19th+century+tennis+tournaments&source=bl&ots=6SE1ULypjh&sig=JC623Xs4UpGTCsaRpaT--i6IJNY&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwitjanr3ffPAhXDMY8KHT6yALsQ6AEIUzAJ#v=onepage&q=notable%2019th%20century%20tennis%20tournaments&f=false|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Gillmeister|first1=Heiner|title=Tennis:Cultural History|date=1998|publisher=A&C Black|location=London|isbn=9780718501952|page=199|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=44Vu3DdHFvsC&pg=PA199&lpg=PA199&dq=william+renshaw+irish+championships&source=bl&ots=toVXc6tkLK&sig=uLonq_PxmWIMtOM08xIqY16ekLg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiWjNOy7vzPAhWIsY8KHYRzBZM4ChDoAQgvMAU#v=onepage&q=william%20renshaw%20irish%20championships&f=false|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Lake|first1=Robert J.|title=A Social History of Tennis in Britain: Volume 5 of Routledge Research in Sports History|date=2014|publisher=Routledge |isbn=9781134445578|page=48|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8kyvBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA41&dq=Important+19th+century+tennis+tournaments&source=gbs_toc_r&cad=3#v=onepage&q&f=false|language=en}}</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#d0f0c0\"\n| National tournaments\n|- style=\"background:#dfe2e9\"\n| State Regional tournaments\n|- style=\"background:#fae7b5\" \n| County tournaments\n|-\n| Local tournaments\n|}\n\n===January to March===\n''No events''\n\n===April===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:85%;\" \n|-\n!width=\"75\"|Date\n!width=\"230\"|Tournament\n!width=\"210\"|Winner\n!width=\"210\"|Finalist\n!width=\"170\"|Semifinalist\n!width=\"170\"|Quarterfinalist\n|-valign=top\n|rowspan=2| 24 April-6 May||style=\"background:#fae7b5\"  rowspan=2|[[Sussex County Lawn Tennis Club Spring Tournament]]<ref>{{cit