s) ||{{flagicon|IRE|1783}} E. J. Wolfe  <br /> || rowspan=2| {{flagicon|IRE|1783}} Arthur Edward Desborough Burke <br /> {{Flagicon|GBR}} W.G. Robinson || rowspan=2|  <br />   <br />   \n|-valign=top\n|Challenger<br /> {{flagicon|IRE|1783}} Robert Baron Templer\n|-valign=top\n|rowspan=2| 24\u201330 October||rowspan=2|[[St. George's Cricket Club Tournament]]<br /> [[New York City]], [[United States]]<br />Outdoor<br />Grass<br />[[St. George's Cricket Club Tournament|Singles]] - [[St. George's Cricket Club Tournament|Doubles]] ||{{flag|Ireland|1783}} John Jameson Cairnes  <br /> 7-5 6-2 6-3||{{Flagicon|USA}} James Rankine || rowspan=2| {{Flagicon|USA}} Charles F. Watson Sr. <br /> 6-1, 6-2 <br /> {{Flagicon|USA}} F. Ennis<br />6-1, 6-1|| rowspan=2| {{Flagicon|USA}} W. P. Anderson <br />6-4 6-3 <br /> {{Flagicon|USA}} R. J. Cross <br /> 6-2 6-3 <br /> {{Flagicon|USA}} H. Henry <br /> 6-2 1-6 6-2<br /> {{Flagicon|USA}} James Rankine <br /> Bye\n|-valign=top\n| || \n|}\n\n===November===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:85%;\" \n|-\n!width=\"75\"|Date\n!width=\"230\"|Tournament\n!width=\"210\"|Winner\n!width=\"210\"|Finalist\n!width=\"170\"|Semifinalist\n!width=\"170\"|Quarterfinalist\n|-valign=top\n|rowspan=2| 4\u201313 November||style=\"background:#dfe2e9\" rowspan=2|[[Victorian Championships]]<br />{{Flagicon|AUS}} [[Melbourne]], [[Australia]]<br />Outdoor<br />Hard<br />[[Victorian Championshipss|Singles]] - [[Victorian Championships|Doubles]] ||{{Flagicon|AUS}} L. Keyser <br />6-4 4-6 6-1 6-1||{{Flagicon|AUS}} Louis Australia Whyte|| rowspan=2| {{Flagicon|AUS}} J. S. Conran <br /> 6-2 6-2 6-4 <br /> {{Flagicon|AUS}} Francis James Highett <br /> Bye|| rowspan=2| {{Flagicon|AUS}} R. H. James <br /> 6-3 6-2 6-1 <br /> {{Flagicon|AUS}} W. M. Mitchell <br />6-0 6-4 1-6 6-3 <br />  {{Flagicon|AUS}} Francis James Highett <br /> W/O <br />  <br /> \n|-valign=top\n| ||\n|}\n\n===December===\n''No events''\n\n==List of tournament winners==\nNote: important tournaments in '''bold'''\n*{{flagicon|Ireland|1783}} Peter Aungier  -Naas -(1)\n*{{flagicon|GBR}} [[Thomas Braddell#Robert Wallace Braddell|Robert W. Braddell]]  - Brighton-Oxford-Lemington Spa-Derby -(4)\n*{{flagicon|GBR}} G. R. Brennan - Edgbaston - (1)\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} Humphrey Berkeley - Teignmouth -(1)\n*{{flagicon|GBR}} George Butterworth - Bath (WOE) - (1)\n*{{flagicon|Ireland|1783}} John Jameson Cairnes  -New York -(1)\n*{{flagicon|USA}} Joseph Sill Clark - Richfield Springs -(1)\n*{{flagicon|GBR}} William Cobbold - East Grinstead - (1)\n*{{flagicon|USA}} Harry F. Connover - New York - (1) \n*{{flagicon|Ireland|1783}} E. J. Charley -Belfast -(1)\n*{{flagicon|GBR}} John William Down - Liverpool -(1)\n*{{flagicon|GBR}} Mark Minden Fenwick - Newcastle -(1)\n*{{flagicon|CAN|1868}} Harry D. Gamble -Toronto -(1)\n*{{flagicon|GBR}} Charles Walder Grinstead - Brentwood- (1)\n*{{flagicon|GBR}} G. F. Hanson -Belfast -(1)\n*{{flagicon|USA}} Lawrence Hobart - Montclair, NJ -(1)\n*{{flagicon|SCO}} John G. Horn - Edinburgh -(1)\n*{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Herbert Lawford]] -Fulham (LAC) -(1)\n*{{flagicon|Ireland|1783}} Michael G. McNamara -Brighton-Waterford- (2)\n*{{flagicon|GBR}} G. M. Minchin -Exeter -(1)\n*{{flagicon|GBR}} William b. Monement -Norwich -(1)\n*{{flagicon|Ireland|1783}} Edward Lysaght - Limerick - (1)\n*{{flagicon|GBR}} [[Ernest Renshaw]] - '''London''' - (1)\n*{{flagicon|GBR}} [[William Renshaw]] -Cheltenham -'''Dublin'''-'''Wimbledon'''- (3)\n*{{flagicon|GBR}} [[Richard Taswell Richardson]] - '''Liverpool''' - (1)\n*{{flagicon|USA}} [[Richard Sears (tennis)|Richard Sears]] -  Newport -(1)\n*{{flagicon|GBR}} Frederick C. Stammer -Lichfield -(1)\n*{{flagicon|GBR}} Charles Sweet - Exmouth - (1)\n*{{flagicon|GBR}} William C. Taylor - Eastbourne - (1)\n*{{flagicon|Ireland|1783}} Richard Barron Templer -Montrose, NJ -(1)\n*{{flagicon|USA}} Alexander Van Rensselear - Hoboken -(1)\n*{{flagicon|GBR}} A. Springett -Darlington -(1)\n*{{flagicon|AUS}} L. Keyser -Melbourne  -(1)