icket Club Tournaments|Doubles]] ||{{flag|Ireland|1783}} John Jameson Cairnes  <br /> 7-5 6-2 6-3||{{Flagicon|USA}} James Rankine || rowspan=2| {{Flagicon|USA}} Charles F. Watson Sr. <br /> 6-1, 6-2 <br /> {{Flagicon|USA}} F. Ennis<br />6-1, 6-1|| rowspan=2| {{Flagicon|USA}} W. P. Anderson <br />6-4 6-3 <br /> {{Flagicon|USA}} R. J. Cross <br /> 6-2 6-3 <br /> {{Flagicon|USA}} H. Henry <br /> 6-2 1-6 6-2<br /> {{Flagicon|USA}} James Rankine <br /> Bye\n|-valign=top\n| || \n|}\n\n===November===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:85%;\" \n|-\n!width=\"75\"|Date\n!width=\"230\"|Tournament\n!width=\"210\"|Winner\n!width=\"210\"|Finalist\n!width=\"170\"|Semifinalist\n!width=\"170\"|Quarterfinalist\n|-valign=top\n|rowspan=2| 4\u201310 November||style=\"background:#dfe2e9\" rowspan=2|[[Victorian Championships]] <ref>{{cite web|title=Intercolonial Lawn Tennis Championships|url=http://trove.nla.gov.au/newspaper/article/11523704|website=|publisher=National Library of Australia, The Argus, Melbourne, 12 November 1881|accessdate=18 July 2016}}</ref><br /> [[Melbourne]], [[Australia]]<br />Outdoor<br />Hard<br />[[Victorian Championships|Singles]] - [[Victorian Championships|Doubles]] ||{{Flagicon|AUS}} Louis Australia Whyte<br />6-4 4-6 6-1 6-1||{{Flagicon|AUS}} Francis James Highett|| rowspan=2| {{Flagicon|AUS}} J. S. Conran <br /> 6-2 6-2 6-4 <br /> {{Flagicon|AUS}} Francis James Highett <br /> Bye|| rowspan=2| {{Flagicon|AUS}} R. H. James <br /> 6-3 6-2 6-1 <br /> {{Flagicon|AUS}} W. M. Mitchell <br />6-0 6-4 1-6 6-3 <br />  {{Flagicon|AUS}} Francis James Highett <br /> W/O <br />  <br /> \n|-valign=top\n| ||\n|}\n\n===December===\n''No events''\n\n==List of tournament winners==\n\nNote: important tournaments in '''bold'''\n*{{flagicon|Ireland|1783}} Richard Barron Templer -Armagh -(1)\n*{{flagicon|GBR}} Pelham George Dunop -Bath -(1)\n*{{flagicon|Ireland|1783}} E. J. Charley -Belfast -(1)\n*{{flagicon|GBR}} Montague Hankey -Bournemouth -(1)\n*{{flagicon|Ireland|1783}