rbert Lawford]]|ENG}}\n|-bgcolor=\"#ffffcc\"\n|3|| align=\"left\" |{{flagathlete|[[Richard Taswell Richardson]]|GBR}}\n|-bgcolor=\"#ffffcc\"\n|4|| align=\"left\" |{{flagathlete| [[Ernest Renshaw]]|ENG}}\n|-bgcolor=\"#ffffcc\"\n|5|| align=\"left\" |{{flagathlete|[[Ernest Browne|Ernest de S. H. Browne]]|Ireland|1783}}\n|-bgcolor=\"#ffffcc\"\n|6|| align=\"left\" |{{flagathlete|[[Otway Woodhouse]]|GBR}}\n|-bgcolor=\"#ffffcc\"\n|7|| align=\"left\" |{{flagathlete|[[Peter Aungier]]|Ireland|1783}}\n|-bgcolor=\"#ffffcc\"\n|8|| align=\"left\" |{{flagathlete|[[Edgar Lubbock]]|GBR}}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[1881 Tennis Season]]\n*[[1881 in sports]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==Sources==\n* ''A Social History of Tennis in Britain: Lake, Robert J. (2014), Volume 5 of Routledge Research in Sports History. Routledge, UK, {{ISBN|9781134445578}}.''\n* ''Ayre's Lawn Tennis Almanack And Tournament Guide, 1908 to 1938, A. Wallis Myers.'' \n* ''British Lawn Tennis and Squash Magazine, 1948 to 1967, British Lawn Tennis Ltd, UK.''\n* ''Dunlop Lawn Tennis Almanack And Tournament Guide, G.P. Hughes, 1939 to 1958, Dunlop Sports Co. Ltd, UK''\n* ''Lawn tennis and Badminton Magazine, 1906 to 1973,  UK.''\n* ''Lowe's Lawn Tennis Annuals and Compendia, Lowe, Sir F. Gordon, Eyre & Spottiswoode''\n* ''Spalding's Lawn Tennis Annuals from 1885 to 1922, American Sports Pub. Co, USA.'' \n* ''Sports Around the World: History, Culture, and Practice, Nauright John and Parrish Charles, (2012), ABC-CLIO, Santa Barbara, Cal, US, {{ISBN|1598843001}}.''\n* ''The Concise History of Tennis, Mazak Karoly, (2010), 6th Edition, 2015.''\n* ''Tennis; A Cultural History, Gillmeister Heiner, (1997), Leicester University Press, Leicester, UK.'' \n* ''The Tennis Book, edited by Michael Bartlett and Bob Gillen, Arbor House, New York, 1981 {{ISBN|0-87795-344-9}}''\n* ''The World of Tennis Annuals, Barrett John, 1970 to 2001.''\n* ''Total Tennis:The Ultimate Tennis Encyclopedia, by Bud Collins, Sport Classic Books, Toronto, Canada, {{ISBN|0-9731443-4-3}}''\n* ''Wright & Ditson Officially Adopted Lawn Tennis Guide's 1890 to 1920 Wright & Ditsons Publishers, Boston, Mass, USA.''\n*''[http://www.tennisarchives.com/jaarwedstrijdenfiche.php http://www.tennisarchives.com/1881 Men's Tennis season]''\n*''[https://app.thetennisbase.com/?enlace=season&anno=1881&tipoMainTorneos=main&surface=&tipo_de_torneo= https://app.thetennisbase.com/1881 Men's Tennis season]''\n\n==External links==\n*http://tennisarchives.com/\n*https://thetennisbase.com/\n\n{{Mens tennis seasons |state=collapsed}}\n\n[[Category:Pre Open era tennis seasons]]\n[[Category:1881 in tennis]]\n", "text_old": "{{ Infobox tennis circuit season\n<!-- Details -->\n| name          = 1881 Men's Tennis tour\n| image         = William Charles Renshaw.jpg\n| image_caption = William Renshaw won most titles this year\n| image_alt     = \n| image_size    = 200px\n| duration      = 23 May \u2013 10 November\n| edition       = 5th\n| tournaments   = 32 (Amateur)\n| categories    = important (5 )<br/>  national (2) <br/> regional/state (10) <br/> county (5) <br/> local (10)\n<!-- Achievements -->\n| most_tournament_titles       = {{flagicon|ENG}} [[William Renshaw]] (4)\n| most_tournament_finals       = {{flagicon|ENG}} [[William Renshaw]] (4)\n| prize_money_leader           = \n| points_leader                = \n<!-- Awards -->\n| player_of_the_year            = \n| most_improved_player_of_the_year = \n| newcomer_of_the_year             = \n| comeback_player_of_the_year      = \n| previous = [[1880 Men's Tennis tour|1880]]\n| next     = [[1882 Men's Tennis tour|1882]]\n}}\nThe '''1881 Men's tennis tour''' <ref>{{cite web|title=Tennis season 1881|url=https://app.thetennisbase.com/?enlace=season&anno=1881&tipoMainTorneos=main&surface=&tipo_de_torneo=|website=thetennisbase.com|publisher=The Tennis Base, 2016|accessdate=9 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Archives|first1=Tennis|title=Tournaments 1881|url=http://www.tennisarchives.com/jaarwedstrijdenfiche.php|website=www.tennisarchives.com|publisher=Tennis Archives, 2016|accessdate=9 December 2016}}</ref> was composed of the fifth annual pre-open era tour now incorporated 32 tournaments staged in [[Australia]], [[Canada]], [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|Great Britain and Ireland]], and the [[United States]]. The [[1881 Wimbledon Championships]] was won by [[William Renshaw]]. This year also saw the inaugural and important [[1881 U.S. National Championships (tennis)|1881 U.S. National Championships]] held at [[Newport Casino]] which [[Richard Sears (tennis)|Richard Sears]] had won.  This was also the year that the [[USTA|United States National Lawn Tennis Association]],<ref>{{cite web|title=USTA HISTORY ARCHIVE|url=https://www.usta.com/About-USTA/Organization/History/USTA_history_archive/|website=usta.com|publisher=USTA|accessdate=17 July 2016}}</ref> which is the world's first national tennis association, was founded. Renshaw then had won two other big tournaments of the year picking up the [[Irish Open (tennis)|Irish Lawn Tennis Championships]] and [[Princes Club Championships]], whilst Richard Taswell Richardson wins the prestigious [[Manchester Open|Northern Championships]].<ref name=\"sports_around_world\">{{cite book |first1=John |last1=Nauright |first2=Charles |last2=Parrish|title=Sports around the world  : history, culture, and practice|date=2012|publisher=ABC-CLIO|location=Santa Barbara, Calif.|isbn=9781598843002|page=198}}</ref>\n\n==Calendar==\n'''Notes 1:''' Challenge Round: the final round of a tournament, in which the winner of a single-elimination phase faces the previous year's champion, who plays only that one match. The challenge round was used in the early history of tennis (from 1877 through 1921),<ref>{{cite web|title=Abolition of Challenge Rounds|url=https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/EP19220320.2.111.2?query=Paris%20International%20Championships|website=paperspast.natlib.govt.nz|publisher=EVENING POST, VOLUME CIII, ISSUE 65, 20 MARCH 1922|accessdate=6 October 2016}}</ref> in some tournaments not all.<center>* Indicates challenger</center>\n'''Notes 2''':''Tournaments in italics were events that were staged only onetime''\n\n===Key===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ffc;\"\n| '''Important tournaments''' <ref>{{cite book|last1=Mazak|first1=Karoly|title=The Concise History of Tennis, The complete tennis history from 1877|date=2016|publisher=Karoly  Mazak|pages=5\u201311|edition=6th|url=http://www.theconcisehistoryoftennis.com/|accessdate=9 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Nauright|first1=John|last2=Parrish|first2=Charles|title=Sports Around the World: History, Culture, and Practice|date=2012|publisher=ABC-CLIO|location=Santa Barbara, Calif.|isbn=9781598843002|page=198|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IkLYDgTnMxEC&pg=RA1-PA198}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Gillmeister|first1=Heiner|title=Tennis:Cultural History|date=1998|publisher=A&C Black|location=London|isbn=9780718501952|page=199|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=44Vu3DdHFvsC&pg=PA199}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Mazak|first1=Karoly|title=The Concise History of Tennis {{!}} The complete tennis history from 1877|date=2010|publisher=Karoly Mazak (Ph.D.)|page=3|edition=6th|url=http://www.theconcisehistoryoftennis.com/}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Lake|first1=Robert J.|title=A Social History of Tennis in Britain: Volume 5 of Routledge Research in Sports History|date=2014|publisher=Routledge |isbn=9781134445578|page=48|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8kyvBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA41}}</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#d0f0c0\"\n| National tournaments\n|- style=\"background:#dfe2e9\"\n| State Regional tournaments\n|- style=\"background:#fae7b5\"\n| County tournaments\n|-\n| Local tournaments\n|}\n\n===January to April===\n''No events''\n\n===May===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:85%;\" \n|-\n!width=\"75\"|Date\n!width=\"230\"|Tournament\n!width=\"210\"|Winner\n!width=\"210